## Frontend environment variables
#
# Local development:
# - Start backend locally (usually http://localhost:5000)
# - Copy this file to .env.local (recommended) or .env
# - Set REACT_APP_API_URL to your backend URL
#
# Vercel:
# - Add the same variable in Project Settings → Environment Variables
# - Set it to your deployed backend URL (e.g. https://your-api.example.com)
#
# VPS (build on server or CI before upload):
# - REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com   (must be public HTTPS in production)
# - REACT_APP_SITE_URL=https://yourdomain.com
#
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
REACT_APP_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

